Pet-Med-AI Alembic migrations

This directory contains the database migration environment for the backend.

Important safety rule:
- Existing local / Render databases were originally created by SQLAlchemy create_all()
  and bootstrap helpers in backend/main.py.
- Do NOT run `alembic upgrade head` against an existing populated database as the
  first operation for this baseline revision.
- For an existing database that already has the current tables, use:
    cd backend
    alembic -c alembic.ini stamp head
- For a new empty database, use:
    cd backend
    alembic -c alembic.ini upgrade head

Alembic V1 establishes version control for the current schema. It intentionally
does not remove the existing startup bootstrap code yet.
